      • getIconDescriptor

        public java.lang.String getIconDescriptor()
        Description copied from interface: ISystemSetupComponent
        get the name of the icon. This returns the name of the icon to display for this component. Use the following code to load the image associated with this icon name. import com.ti.ccstudio.ui.target.config.TargetConfigUtils; String iconName = setupComponent.getIconDescriptor(); Image image = TargetConfigUtils.getImage(TargetConfigUtils.getTypeFromDBDescription(iconName)); The name of the icon represents a combinantion of both the type of the component and state of the component; for example, a bypassed cpu.
        Specified by:

        name of icon to display; for example, "cpu", "nondebug", etc...

      • getDecoratedLabelText

        public java.lang.String getDecoratedLabelText()
        Description copied from interface: ISystemSetupComponent
        get decorated text to display This returns the decorated text to display to the user, typically through a labelProvider. Decorated text includes "(bypassed)" suffix for cpus that are bypassed. The decorated text is identical to what the Configuration Editor displays in it's advanced tree.
        Specified by:

        Returns:
